Broadband Equipment Code of Conduct – Version 6.0 27

February 10th 2017

C.1.2 USB dongles
For a home gateway with USB ports additional functionality originally not built into the device can also be provided via USB dongles. The power consumption of USB dongles is measured at the DC 5V USB interface.
For a home gateway with an internal USB device, the power budget shall include the value of the USB device defined in table 13 multiplied by a factor of (1/0.84) plus the USB value for the interface defined in table 11 (also see note 11.3).
Please note that the USB devices are considered as not equipped with additional chipsets implementing applications or complex software stacks that will drastically change the power values.
