(17.3) L2.1 low power state (with two sub-states: L2.1N and L2.1B) allows substantial reduction in power consumption and is primarily intended for support of VoIP, while other services are unused. L2.2 low power state is intended for keep-alive applications during multi-hour battery backup and it implements significant reduction of power consumption (resulting in extremely reduced data rate and loss of QoS).

